label: Newton Plantation Rent Book 1868
description: This book contains records of  yearly and weekly renters, comprehensive inventories of movable items and cattle, as well as increases in the stock of horses and mules. It also incorporates the day book for 1868 and records some of the daily activities on the plantation. This book was used as somewhat of a multi purpose book as it also gives an account of the standings of accounts and transactions with some listed companies  such as G.W. McClean & Co., Michael Greaves, John Alleyne & Co., M.L.Croney  as well as Nightengale & Co.  Also included is a list of plantation workers who were caught stealing from the plantation and were sentenced to time in prison. It then goes on to detail deliveries of rum, sugar and molasses produced on the plantation and sold to customers.
